newsitem.title: USA: U.S. spot jet ends higher, led by sharp NYMEX jump.
newsitem.headline: U.S. spot jet ends higher, led by sharp NYMEX jump.

text.p: U.S. spot jet fuel prices surged higher with the rally on the NYMEX Monday and the modest gains in New York Harbor (NYH) differentials.
January heating oil futures prices on the NYMEX lept higher, following the sharp gains in the gasoline futures on supply concerns and technical buying interest.
NYH prompt 54-grade barrels changed hands at 3.50 cents over the NYMEX, according to traders, though overall activity remained thin.
NYH low-sulphur 55-grade was talked at 4.50 cents over the screen, though the figure remained notional, traders said.
